{"lemma":"مَآتِمُ","slug":"مَآتِمُ","root":"#.ت.م","root_slug":"_-ت-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ت-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n144"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A2%D8%AA%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a place where women are gathered","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mourning ceremony"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a religious practice of mourning Hussain ibn Ali associated with Ashura","tags":["Shia"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"husayniyya, a place where ma'tam is held","tags":["Shia","regional"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the root ء ت م (ʔ t m)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n144","headword_ar":"مَاْتَمٌ","root":"Atm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atama","text_ar":"اَتَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the last of the senses explained above. (Msb.) [Thus it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A staying, remaining, dwelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place. But it more commonly signifies] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assembling"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women [and of men also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a case of rejoicing"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mourning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 234.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":14},{"kind":"text","text":"It is also a noun of time from the same. (Msb.) [Thus it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time of staying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] ―         -b3-  And it is also a noun of place from the same. (Msb.) [And thus it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of staying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. But it more commonly signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of assembling"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women [and of men also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a case of rejoicing"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mourning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atima","text_ar":"اَتِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Khálid Ibn-Yezeed. (T.) ―         -b4-  And hence, tropically, (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women assembling together"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a case of rejoicing"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a case of good"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any assembly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of women,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a case of mourning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rejoicing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of young women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) accord. to some; but it is not so: and some assert that the word is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atomN","text_ar":"اَتْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the first of the senses explained in this art.; and from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atuwmN","text_ar":"اَتُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to a woman; because it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women coming together, and meeting face to face, in a case of good"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA=timu","text_ar":"مَا=تِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh.) Abu-l-'Atà Es-Sindee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Ea$iy~apa qaAma Aln~aAy^iHaAtu wa $uq~iqato\n                      \n                     \n                        juyuwbN biA^ayodiY maA^otamK wa xuduwdu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the evening when arose the wailing women"},{"kind":"text","text":"to wail,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and openings at the necks and bosoms"},{"kind":"text","text":"of garments"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were rent with the hands of assembled"},{"kind":"text","text":"mourning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women, and cheeks"},{"kind":"text","text":"also were lacerated]: (S, M, Mgh:) i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^ayodiY nisaA='K","text_ar":"بِاَيْدِى نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And another says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Hat~aY taraAhun~a ladayohi quy~amaA\n                      \n                     \n                        kamaA taraY Hawola AlA^amiyri AlmA^otamaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So that thou seest them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(referring to women)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing in his presence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, it, like as thou seest the assembly of men around the prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commander"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmA^tm","text_ar":"الماتم"},{"kind":"text","text":"here necessarily denoting men. (M.) ―         -b5-  IKt says, (Msb,) it is used by the vulgar to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil accident;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb;) [and Mtr adds,] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wailing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA fiY maA_otami falaAnK","text_ar":"كُنَّا فِى مَاـْتَمِ فَلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were present at the affliction of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA fiY maA^otami baniy fulalnK","text_ar":"كُنَّا فِى مَاْتَمِ بَنِي فُلَلنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were present at the affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wailing, of the sons of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) but the correct word in this case, (S, Mgh,) or the better, (Msb,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAHap","text_ar":"مَنَاحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb:) so says IAmb. (Mgh.) But accord. to IB, nothing forbids that it may occur in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of wailing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wailing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weeping;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for therefore do women assemble: and thus it may be in the saying of Et-Teymee, respecting Mansoor Ibn-Ziyád,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wa Aln~aAsu maA^otamuhumo Ealayohi waAHidN\n                      \n                     \n                        fiY kl~i daArK ran~apN wa zafiyru"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people's mourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for him was one: in every house was a moaning, and a sighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in the saying of another,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aDoHaY banaAtu Als~ubiY~i A_i*o qutiluwA\n                      \n                     \n                        fiY maA^otamK waAls~ibaAEu fiY Eurusi"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The daughters of the captives, when they were slain, became, in the early part of the day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state mourning; and the beasts of prey, in a state of rejoicing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","T","S","M","Mgh","K"]}]}}